Compares two strings, returning a true response if and only if they contain the same sequence of characters. A null string is considered to be equal to an empty string.

Inputs\:
string1 - The first string.
string2 - The second string.
ignoreCase - If set to 'true', then the comparison ignores case considerations. The two strings are considered equal ignoring case if they are of the same length and corresponding characters in the two strings are equal ignoring case. If set to any value other than 'true', then the strings must match exactly to be considered equal.

responses\:
true - If the two strings are equal
false - If the two strings are not equal

4521d00c-b995-4900-8811-0c8b01c67dcf.description=
Synopsis

    This flow creates NAS port configurations.
    buildSusNasFgNetPortConfig performs the following steps\:
      1. Compare two strings of data, returning "true" if the strings are the same.
      2. Using the HPOO flow getNetPorts, retrieve a list of ports for configuration.
      3. Iterate through and compare the ports for ports matching the input criteria.
      4. Create a list of home node physical ports.
      5. Using the HPOO flow getNumNetLifsPerPhysPortByFgParityList, retrieve a list of LIFs based on the physical port.
      6. Retireve a partner node.
      7. Using the HPOO flow getNetPorts, retrieve a list of ports for configuration of the partner node.
      8. Iterate through and compare the ports for ports matching the input criteria.
      9. Create a list of partner node physical ports.
    10. Using the HPOO flow getNumNetLifsPerPhysPortByFgParityList, retrieve a list of LIFs based on the physical port.
    11. Create failover groups for the NAS ports.

Input

    clusterName - The IP or host name of the NetApp cluster (required).
      Valid values\: Dot-decimal notation IPv4 address or RFC 1123 compliant host name.
      Default value\: None.

    homeNode - The contoller node for the clusterName (required).
    homePhysicalPort - The actual port that the LIF is assigned to (required).
    vlanId - The name of the vLan used in the flow (required).
    homeVlanPort - 
    failoverGroup - The failover group assigned to the cluster (required).
      Valid values\: Implementation-specific.
      Default value\: 

    fgRegexExclude -
      Valid values\: 
      Default value\: 

    includeOnlyLinkStatusUp - (required).
      Valid values\: 
      Default value\: 

    elementDelimiter - (required).
      Valid values\: 
      Default value\: 

    tokenDelimiter - (required).
      Valid values\: 
      Default value\: 

    overrideJRAS - Value to override the system defined Java RAS server.
      Valid values\: Implementation specific.
      Default value\: Hosting Eng RAS.

Results

    hpooFlowResult - The XML response specific to the functionality of the flow; returned as a success or failure.  See Notes section for more details.
    flowStatus - Overall status of the flow, value is one of the string literals "success" or "failed".

Responses

    Success - All operations and subflows completed successfully.
    Failure - Some operations and/or subflows failed.

Notes

    1. Anything else the caller or support person may need to know about the flow. Relationships that aren't easily inferred, abmnormal flow behaviors, hard-codings, etc.
